- **Content hydration:** Extract and synthesize content from the `contents/` folder and PDF/Word assets. For PDF images use `tools/python/extract_pdf_images.py` (orientation correction): `--pdf contents/<file>.pdf --out assets/pdf-extracted` and optional `--page 5` or `--page 3,5-7` when multiple PDFs exist. **After extract or any new large image:** run `python tools/python/compress_web_assets.py` — see `docs/guides/IMAGE_COMPRESSION_GUIDE.md`. Structure spec: `config/outline.md` + `docs/guides/OUTLINE_GUIDE.md`.
- **Image compression (mandatory):** `docs/guides/IMAGE_COMPRESSION_GUIDE.md` + `tools/python/compress_web_assets.py` — any JPEG/PNG/WebP placed under `assets/` that is **≥ 80 KB** or has longest edge **> 1920 px** MUST be compressed before referencing in HTML or finishing the task. Never commit multi-MB photos/screenshots. After `extract_pdf_images.py`, always run compress script. Updating `cover-title.png` requires regenerating `cover-title.webp`. Skip `test-*`, `debug-*`, `pdf-page-*-preview*`.
- For text, you may reasonably expand based on industry common sense when source material is thin.
- You may extend **`styles/style-guide/*.css`** when needed; keep `docs/guides/style_guide.md`, `styles/style-guide/README.md`, and `docs/guides/style_guide_extended.md` in sync.

# 2. Asset & Image Management (No Hallucination)
- **Zero fake links:** Do NOT invent or guess external image URLs.
- **Compress large images (CRITICAL):** Before adding or replacing assets in HTML, compress per `docs/guides/IMAGE_COMPRESSION_GUIDE.md`. Run `python tools/python/compress_web_assets.py` after PDF extract or when importing photos. Targets: JPEG q82, max edge 1920px, production files ≥ 80 KB must shrink; no uncompressed multi-MB sources in `assets/`.
- **Placeholders:** When no local image exists, use a grey `.image-placeholder` div with descriptive text. Prefer real extracted assets; minimize placeholders when PDF images are available.
- **Placeholder format:** `[Image Placeholder: detailed description of subject, style, and layout]`
- **WeChat / chat screenshots:** Default to `.chat-shot` with `object-fit: contain` (no crop). Use `.chat-shot-trim-x` only when intentional horizontal trim (~4%) is needed.
- **Grid count:** Match image count to grid cells (2 images → `.image-grid-duo` or 2-column gallery, not 4 empty cells).

# 3. Interactive & Game Elements
- Encourage purposeful interactivity (matching games, canvas backgrounds, etc.) when appropriate.
- **Event propagation (CRITICAL):** Inside `.interactive-zone`, games, and canvas demos, call `event.stopPropagation()` (and `preventDefault` where needed) on **pointer** events (`mousedown`, `mouseup`, `click`, `touchstart`, `touchend`) and **keyboard** nav keys (Space, arrows, PageUp/Down) so clicks do not trigger Reveal navigation. **Do not** block `wheel` — deck flip uses `shared/scripts/slide-wheel-nav.js` at capture phase; blocking `wheel` in a child breaks scroll-to-advance after interacting (see `docs/guides/WHEEL_NAV_GUIDE.md`).
- Avoid heavy high-resolution animations, large canvas loops, or embedded iframes unless the user explicitly requires them. **B 站视频嵌入**须遵循 `docs/guides/BILIBILI_EMBED_GUIDE.md`（仅用 `player.bilibili.com`，禁止 iframe 主站页）。
- Complex logic lives in `scripts/` (deck-specific) and `shared/scripts/` (cross-site) — not inline in `index.html`.

# 4. Presentation Structure (Reveal.js)
- **Linear navigation:** Project uses `navigationMode: 'linear'`; keyboard ↑/↓ disabled. Audience advances horizontally only.
- **Nested sections:** Use parent `<section>` stacks to group related slides in HTML; they still count as flat leaf pages in linear mode. Do not rely on vertical down-navigation for the audience.
- **Built-in transition:** Reveal `transition: 'none'`. Per-slide enter FX via `SlideTransitionFX` — follow `docs/guides/transition_guide.md`.
- **New chapter slides:** Add `data-transition-tier="key"` on openers; ordinary content pages use the default NORMAL pool (17/14/11 cycle).
- **Speaker notes:** Dense explanations and presenter cues go in `<aside class="notes">`, not on the visual slide.

# 5. Code Specifications & Modularity
- **No inline styles** except dynamic JS coordinates.
- **CSS classes only** from `style_guide.css` / `styles/style-guide/*.css` (or newly added documented classes).
- Every content slide wraps body in `.slide-content-layer`.
- **Unified content-page titles:** Put page title as the **first** `h2` inside `.slide-content-layer` (or wrap in `.slide-page-header`). Class the slide `.content-slide`. Do **not** add inline font sizes. Exceptions — no auto-fit: `.title-slide`, `.slide-agenda`, `.section-opener`, `.slide-closing`.
- Modular JS in `scripts/` and `shared/scripts/`; bump `?v=` query params in HTML when changing script or CSS files.
- **Bilibili embed:** 新增或修改 B 站视频页前先读 `docs/guides/BILIBILI_EMBED_GUIDE.md`；`data-bilibili-embed` + `scripts/cases/bilibili-embed.js`，`slidechanged` 懒加载。
- **Canvas lazy loading:** Stop off-slide grid canvases on `slidechanged` (see `scripts/core/deck-slide-host.js` pattern).
- **Title fit debugging:** If titles look too small, check `--slide-title-font-max` is high enough (see `docs/guides/style_guide.md` §4.4) and that `fitSlidePageTitles()` runs after layout (`clientWidth > 0`). Never lower `--slide-title-font-max` to “fix” overflow — the JS should clamp via `--slide-title-fit-size`.

# 6. Local Preview & LAN Sharing
- **Required before preview or verification:** Run `start-lan-server.bat` from the project root (double-click, or `.\start-lan-server.bat` in terminal). Do not open slides via `file://`, and do not start ad-hoc `python -m http.server` unless the bat is unavailable.
- `start-lan-server.bat` starts HTTP on port 8080 (`--bind 0.0.0.0`), auto-opens `http://localhost:8080/` in the default browser, and prints LAN URLs for same-network devices.
- For localhost-only quick preview (no LAN exposure), use `start-local-server.bat` instead.
- Reveal.js loads from jsDelivr CDN — clients need internet access.
